// CP systems — consistency over availability
// ZooKeeper: refuses requests during partition (leader election)
// HBase, etcd: rejects writes if quorum unreachable
// Use for: distributed locks, leader election, config management

// AP systems — availability over consistency
// Cassandra: always accepts writes, resolves conflicts later
// DynamoDB (default): eventually consistent reads
// DNS: serves cached/stale records during partition
// Use for: user sessions, shopping carts, social feeds

